e Symbiocene.With the current and coming generations, "Generation Symbiocene," Albrecht sees reason for optimism. The battle between the forces of destruction and the forces of creation will be won by Generation Symbiocene, and Earth Emotions presents an ethical and emotional odyssey for that victory.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aEmotionsxHealth aspects. 0aEnvironmentalismxPhilosophy. 0aHuman ecologyxPhilosophy. 0aNaturexEffect of human beings on. 4aEnvironmental History. 4aPhilosophy. 4aPsychology & Psychiatry.  abiophilia.  aforces of creation.  ageneration symbiocene.  asolastalgia, ecolinguistics.  atopophilia.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065198040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501715242?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501715242423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501715242/original  a978-3-11-065198-0  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles